{"key":"processedPost-6605100","value":{"id":6605100,"first":6604667,"last":6605798,"when":1172335278,"utime":"02/24/07 06:41 PM","content":"If you have a bicycle tire or phone book, you can bang the jar a few times against it and each individual kernel will separate from each other kernel.  This allows you to pour the grains from one jar to the other without handling.  You also have individual grains to spread out as they inoculate your new jar instead of a clump from a spoon.<br />RR","title":"Re: G2G - Shaking vs. Spoonscraping","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}